                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/618: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Officer in Chargé at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-09T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 9, 1942—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>332. Reference is made to Kabul’s no. 22, July 4, 4 p.m., repeated to your
                    office. After consultation with the American military authorities in India, if
                    you perceive no objection thereto, please inform Thayer under what auspices the
                    plane operated and request him so to advise the Afghan Government.</p>
                <p>Please repeat to Kabul as Dept.’s No. 10.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
